clan.description: This is a laid back guild best suited for people who take a casual approach on this server - if this is not your main city, or you don't have a lot of time for the game in general, you'll like it here. clan.description: This is a laid back guild best suited for people who take a casual approach on this server - if this is not your main city, or you don't have a lot of time for the game in general, you'll like it here. If our philosophy works for you, you'll like it here. And we exist on every server, with many people with us on multiple worlds.

clan.name: U. S. Veterans
clan.description: We would like to welcome you to the Guild,"US Veterans". We are open to everyone and especially those members and families of the US Armed Forces current and past. We're a tight knit group of players dedicated to helping one another grow their cities, compete in GBG and GE, and have fun doing it. We have a 1.9 Thread and also we do have access to several external 1.9 threads. We have Swap Threads, Stix to Brix Thread, Tips and Tricks thread, Question and Answer Thread and an End of Level Thread.These are the established Guidelines designed specifically to help each member succeed:We ask all of our members to participate in our Guild Expedition and Guild Battle Ground. We require upon reaching Iron Age that each player will complete Level 1 in GE each session. Recommended you complete as many Levels as your standing allows. Get those awards.We require upon reaching Iron Age at least 2 Battles (either Attack or Negotiation) each day per session in GBG.It is understood Real Life comes first and not everyone can play each day, therefore a Private Message (PM) to our leadership will alleviate being Kicked from the Guild. Inactivity or Non-participation for longer than 7 days, you'll be Kicked from the Guild to make room for other players. If Real Life causes you to miss 7 days or more please PM Leadership for guidance.There will be NO Sniping of fellow Guild Members GBs, this will be grounds for being Kicked from the Guild.No Flipping fellow Guild members GBs without thier permission.Swap Threads instructions can be found under the same titled threads on the message board. Vilolating established Swap Thread rules will result in being released.You must have an Obsevatory GB after reaching Iron Age and an Atonium or an Arc GB as soon as possible thereafter to help with the Guild Treasury to build Seige Camps and other buildings in GBG and to open GE Levels.If you have any questions or need help please post on the established thread, we have plenty of players with great knowledge of the game.Please be respectful, succeed and have fun.
